article.headline: Quinnipiac 92, Concordia College 77
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. (AP) -- Chris Wehye tied a career-high with 19 points while pulling down 12 rebounds as Quinnipiac defeated Concordia, 92-77 Wednesday night. Wehye hit on 8-of-12 from the floor, and Karl Anderson finished with 15 points, hitting on 6-of-9 from the field, and 10 rebounds as well as two blocks. Concordia (0-1) led 29-17 over the final eight minutes led by William Cherry and Richard Fields. Cherry finished with a game-high 28 points, hitting on 9-of-12 from long range and 3-of-5 from three-point range. He also hit on 7-of-9 from the free throw line. Fields totaled 19 points, hitting 6-of-13 from the floor and 4-of-9 from the outside. Quinnipiac (1-1) broke a 14-14 tie at 13:39 in the first half.
